# Trivy allowlist for HIGH/CRITICAL findings the gate cannot fix in P6.
# Each entry must reference a tracking note + revisit trigger.
#
# Format: one CVE per line. Comments allowed via leading `#`.

# ─── Express 4.x dependency lock-in ──────────────────────────────────────
# `path-to-regexp` is pinned by Express 4.x router internals (0.1.7) and
# by `swagger-ui-express` (0.2.5). Bumping forces an Express 5 / NestJS 11
# migration; tracked separately. Re-evaluate when the Express 5 PR lands.
CVE-2024-45296    # path-to-regexp 0.1.7 + 0.2.5
CVE-2024-52798    # path-to-regexp 0.1.7
CVE-2026-4867     # path-to-regexp 0.1.7

# ─── multer 1.x lock-in via @nestjs/platform-express 10.x ───────────────
# NestJS 10 uses multer 1.4.5-lts.1; multer 2.x has breaking API changes.
# Cleared by upgrading to NestJS 11 + multer 2.x in a follow-up.
CVE-2025-7338
CVE-2025-48997
CVE-2025-47944
CVE-2025-47935
CVE-2026-3520     # also affects 2.0.2 path; overrides will catch new releases
CVE-2026-3304
CVE-2026-2359

# ─── lodash future-dated CVE referencing non-existent fix version ───────
# Trivy reports fix in 4.18.0 which has not been published. Re-evaluate
# when that version exists upstream.
CVE-2026-4800

